        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-29 14:41:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI wonder if it wouldn't be better to use interfaces instead of \"authorative\" models.  The interfaces would go in models-xxx, possibly along with a provider that provides implementations for JSON-decoding purposes.  The JPA provider can have its own implementations, that are returned from queries, and does the mapping from interface to JPA object when doing creates/updates.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
