          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-29 14:44:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> I wonder if it wouldn't be better to use interfaces instead of\n > \"authorative\" models.  The interfaces would go in models-xxx,\n > possibly along with a provider that provides implementations for\n > JSON-decoding purposes.  The JPA provider can have its own\n > implementations, that are returned from queries, and does the\n > mapping from interface to JPA object when doing creates/updates.\n\nUsing interfaces would also eliminate the need to have a models-pap flavor and a models-pdp flavor of the classes, one representing external objects and one internal.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
